subject: p19182863
Findings: Comparison is made to previous study from. There is unchanged cardiomegaly. There are again seen bilateral pleural effusions, right side worse than left. Underlying consolidation at that location cannot be excluded. Effusion on the left has improved slightly. There is some mild prominence of pulmonary interstitial markings without overt fluid overload. No pneumothoraces are seen.
